g.text: Game Name: Bird Flu Simulator
A game where you play as a virus that has infected a chicken. You goal
is to infect the world. The game has three phases:
* Phase 1: Barn Infection
This is played in first person mode in the viewpoint of the infected chicken.
You tap on the screen or use the mouse to target other chickens and
shoot out fecal matter to infect them. You only have a set amount of time
per day to infect other chickens, and you need to avoid being caught by the farmer.
At the end of the day, you can choose to upgrade the potency of your
virus. The more infections you do the more mutation points you'll have
to upgrade your virus. The upgrade UI is shown as a radial selection
over the screen, with 4 options.
* Phase 2: Barn Escape
If you infect 75% of the chickens, the farmer open the bar doors,
allowing you to escape. The game zooms out to an isometric mode,
showing the chicken in third-person and the whole farm with several other barns.
Each farm shows dots inside them representing what animals are inside the barn,
such as cows, chickens and pigs. Your goal is to stay in as many barns as you can
before the farmers catch you. The longer you stay inside a barn, the more animals
you infect, with each dot turning red as they are infected.
Cows are harder to infect, and pigs are the hardest. You need to spend more time
in the barn to infect them.
Once you've infected 100% of all pigs, you unlock a new virus mutation, and move to
Phase 3.
Phase 3: World Domination
In this phase, the game becomes a top-down shooter. The mutated virus now has
infected a migrating wild bird, and you now control the bird as it flies across
farmland, mountains and oceans. You have to shoot fecal matter into barns as you see them
to spread the infection.
You have to avoid predators and try to reach the end of the map. Your goal is to
infect as many of the barns as you can, if you infect more than 75% you win the game.
